2. cs.CY (Computers and Society) - The paper touches upon the socio-economic factors that drive international research collaboration, which is relevant to the intersection of computers and society. The authors also mention the policy and management implications of their findings, which is relevant to this sub-category. 

3. cs.DL (Digital Libraries) - The paper discusses the patterns of collaboration among countries in Africa, which can be seen as a form of digital library. The authors also mention the importance of analyzing history, culture, and language, which are relevant to the preservation and curation of digital content. 

4. cs.SD (Software Engineering) - The paper does not directly discuss software engineering, but it does touch upon the management of international research collaboration, which can be seen as a form of project management. 

5. cs.IR (Information Retrieval) - The paper does not directly discuss information retrieval, but it does touch upon the analysis of subjective human factors, which is relevant to the user-centered approach of information retrieval.
